<IFRAME FRAMEBORDER=1 ALIGN=CENTER width=100% HEIGHT=200 SCROLLING=YES SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/Forum21/HTML/002169.html">
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#000050"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Grogan G</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I need a new weapon so I can taunt more effectivley.  Does anyone have info on the Gigantic Zweihander?  Does it still drop?  Can a group of 2 (me L31 & L45 Wiz) take Karg?  Any hints/experiences appreciated.<P>Cheers,<P>Grogan<BR>Povar</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Ruatha</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">One of the things I discovered while hunting giants is that you can't taunt as effectively with a 2-hander as you can with 2 1-handers.  If you want to taunt effectively, get a couple of fast one-handers and go to town.<BR><P>------------------<BR>Ruatha Kneeslasher &lt;Wings of Honor&gt;<BR>39th Level Gnome Warriorette</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Immudan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I don't think you can really make a blanket statement like that Ruatha.  The viability of 1h versus 2h changes according to what weapons you have available and what level you are.  In my low 30s my choice of weapons was Dragoon Dirk and Ashenwood Short Spear or Langesaxe of the  Wolves.  At this point in my adventures my LotW was outdamaging and out taunting my dual wield weapons by a significant amount.<P>At high levels I agree with you.  I'm 1 bubble from 46 now and I'm beginning to wonder why I carry my Exe Axe still (yeah I know, damage shields).  I do considerably more damage with my Painbringer and my EB Mace.  I'm still trying to get a group together to help me get some Yaks or a couple of EBWs.<P>It was my experience that from 1 to whatever level we get DW at (13?) 2h is better.  From DW level to about level 20 DW is better because of the damage cap.  From about 20 to about 30 2h is better because the damage cap gets lifted but you can't get a double attack in your off hand.  From 30 to about 40 it depends on your weapons and begins to get more skewed towards DW because of the level bonus.  From about 40 on DW is better unless your 2h weapon is MUCH better than your DW weapons.<P>------------------<BR>Khumak - 45 Ogre Warrior<BR>Hasima - 8 Dark Elf Necro<BR>Immudan - 11 Erudite Wizard<BR>(Rodcet Nife)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Elldog</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">DW is much better for taunting from my experience.<P>One thing to keep in mind though is that if you DW, your chances of being riposted on go up 2 to 3 times.  When you are fighting an NPC that has a high defensive skills and can hit for 100+, this becomes a factor.<P>Elldog<BR>50th Warrior<BR>RN</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Martigahn</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Very True Elldog ... I did not think about that but , hehe, this makes me even more happy with the Mithril 2 handed sword.<P>Reguarding the taunt issue, it seems I taunt better with dual wield Ykesha than with Mithril 2H but not that much.<P>Usually we can say the offensive proc of a weapon pisses off the MOB ... if you want a good taunt, Ykeshas make it or any offensive procing weapon (bloodfire ??? lol)<P>Fafrd.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
</IFRAME>
</FONT>
